# PartnerOrderProcess Review

## Findings
1. [P2] Fix 1 — Channel filter dead code still exists. `CHANNEL_FILTERS` is still declared at lines 35-40 and `ChannelFilter` is still implemented at lines 582-630, but there is no JSX usage of `<ChannelFilter>` anywhere in `partnerorderprocess.jsx`. FIX: delete `CHANNEL_FILTERS` and the entire `ChannelFilter` function.
2. [P1] Fix 2 — `FixedStageRow` is still the old card-and-toggle component. The row still accepts `toggleBusyKey` and `onToggle` at line 636, renders full-width cards with text channel badges at lines 730-745, and shows the inline active toggle plus pencil action at lines 700-727 instead of the required compact desktop row and mobile accordion. Locked stages also still render a pencil button when `slot.canEdit` is true. The parent still uses `toggleBusyKey` state at line 1076 and passes `onToggle={handleToggleStage}` at lines 1609-1616, so there is no `expandedKey` state or one-row accordion behavior. FIX: replace `FixedStageRow` with the compact row/mobile accordion version, add `expandedKey` state in `OrderProcessContent`, and update the `.map()` call to pass `isExpanded`, `onToggleExpand`, and `onEdit` only.
3. [P2] Fix 3 — The mobile channel legend was not added. The render goes from the current-process summary directly into the stage list container at lines 1587-1618, and there is no `sm:hidden` legend block explaining the hall/pickup/delivery icons before the `bg-white rounded-xl border overflow-hidden` list. FIX: insert the mobile-only channel legend immediately before the stage-list container.
4. [P1] Fix 4 — `LOCAL_UI_TEXT` still drives user-facing copy instead of `t()`. The hardcoded object is still defined at lines 125-135. `analyzeStageSet()` still returns localized Russian strings through `LOCAL_UI_TEXT.*` at lines 249, 258, 267, and 276, the blocker UI still renders `LOCAL_UI_TEXT.blockerGeneric` and raw `stageAnalysis.blocker` at lines 1505-1508, and the current-process label still uses `LOCAL_UI_TEXT.currentProcess` at line 1589. The old row also still uses `LOCAL_UI_TEXT.locked`, `LOCAL_UI_TEXT.enabled`, and `LOCAL_UI_TEXT.disabled` at lines 698 and 712. FIX: replace out-of-row usages with `t('...')`, make `analyzeStageSet()` return i18n keys, render blockers with `t(stageAnalysis.blocker)`, and remove `LOCAL_UI_TEXT` only after the `FixedStageRow` replacement eliminates the remaining row-local references.
5. [P3] Fix 5 — Dead stage-management handlers are still present. `handleAddStage`, `handleDeleteStage`, `handleConfirmDelete`, `handleMoveUp`, and `handleMoveDown` are still declared at lines 1229, 1326, 1331, 1365, and 1390, but they have no JSX or prop usages in this file. FIX: remove those handler declarations, keep `deleteMutation`, `deleteDialog`, and `moveBusy` only if they must remain for hook-order safety, and add the reserved comment described in Fix 5.

## Summary
Total: 5 findings (0 P0, 2 P1, 2 P2, 1 P3)

## Prompt Clarity
- Overall clarity: 3
- Ambiguous Fix descriptions: Fix 4B conflicts with the outer page-folder-only review scope because the dictionary lives elsewhere.
- Missing context: It was unclear whether the task wanted a review of the current file against the redesign spec or a review of an already-patched candidate.
- Scope questions: It was unclear whether implementation-only instructions in the embedded prompt should be ignored during review-only mode.
